Alexei Miller of Gazprom calls Pipeline beginning of a new gas era in Bulgaria
The start of building of the South-stream-pipeline in Bulgaria represents the start of one of the greatest European energy projects, declared the Gazprom executive board.
„The present event is a milestone: The construction works at the Bulgarian section of the South-stream gas pipeline, the greatest and most important project in Europe, "began", said the executive board chairperson of Gazprom, Alexei Miller, on Thursday in a declaration
The project is a key element for the energy security of the entire European continent.
South Stream is supposed to guarantee for more variety with the case of Russia's export routes through Europe.
A contract quarrel between Gazprom and his counterparts in Ukraine in which the majority of the Russian gas is stored for Europe guarantees for an increased risk with the case of conventional routes as people are to hear about official page
Miller who means direct connection to Bulgaria, a member of the European Union, said that the geopolitical risks associated with transit countries are „forever" off.
Bulgarian consumers receive gas of South Stream to vergünstigten rates if the entire project goes in 2015 in operation.
According to Gazprom the construction works are supposed to begin in other subordinate countries on the planned route to the end of the year.
The pipeline is laid out onto an annual capacity from 62.3 billion cubic meters of natural gas.
